node.text:
Kloof House, a short film that explores the idea of indoors and outdoors coexisting. A family home positioned below Lion’s Head, reinforcing the connection to nature and its cycles.
Share this video with someone who needs to see this project!
.
_architecture: @_saota 
_interior designers: @_arrcc
_interior decor: @__okha 
_director and producer: @tatjanameirelles 
_soundtrack: @moodship_
_landscape designer: @franchescawatson 
_structural engineers: moroff & kühne consulting engineers
_quantity surveyor: @sbdsqs 
_main contractor: gossow & harding construction pty (ltd)
.

.

#architecture_hunter 
Accordingly to @omniviewdesign, “the main ambition behind the design of the Villa, was to create a home that combines a strong sense of centricity with flowing connections to its natural environment.

To achieve this, the model of the ancient Greek home was studied carefully as a departure point. In fact, the massing and master planning of spiral Villa Is very close to the ancient Greek home.

The ancient Greek geometry of the spiral has been used to organize and Reinvent this master plan as a sequence of activities. The flow of the spiral represents a spectrum from private to public and ends in the Centrepoint.

There, The Villa features an abstraction or the ancient Greek "Hestia", which in this case is materialized as a central exterior sitting under the shade of an olive tree.

This way the goal of the ancient Greek house to offer privatized exterior space is realized, but at the same time strong relationships to the peripheral functions are created •
.
.
.
.
.
.

This year, due to the COVID-19 Pandemic, Casacor, an exhibition of architecture, design and decoration that takes place annually in several cities in Brazil and the world, had to be different.

#CasacorJanelas invited several architects and designers to design spaces inside containers, placed in different spots of the city.

In this edition, LG @lgdobrasil proposed Suite Arquitetos @suite_arquitetos to design the “Connected House”, the container located in Praça Cidade de Milão, with landscape designing by Bia Abreu @biaabreu_paisagismo. 

In the kitchen, the architects specified the LG Studio Line appliances, in addition to the Smart LG Side by Side Inverter refrigerator. In the living room, they artistically composed the wall with frames and also with: the LG 65 ”4K OLED HDR Smart TV, awarded as the best TV on the market, the mirrored Artcool air conditioning and the Multi Artcool Gallery.

“LG Connected House” also has other sophisticated products of the brand. Check everything else here: lg.com/br/casa-cor

————

Neste ano, por conta da Pandemia do COVID-19, a Casacor, uma mostra de arquitetura, design e decoração que acontece anualmente em várias cidades do Brasil e do mundo, teve que ser diferente. 

A Casacor Janelas propôs convidar diversos arquitetos e designers para projetarem espaços dentro de containers, espalhados em toda a cidade. 

Nesta edição a LG @lgdobrasil chamou a Suíte Arquitetos @suite_arquitetos para desenhar a “Casa Conectada LG”, cujo container fica na Praça Cidade de Milão, com projeto paisagístico de Bia Abreu @biaabreu_paisagismo. 

Na cozinha, os arquitetos especificaram os eletrodomésticos da Linha Studio LG, além da geladeira Smart LG Side by Side Inverter. 
Já na sala de estar, artisticamente entre os quadros compuseram a parede com: a Smart TV LG 65” 4K OLED HDR, eleita a melhor TV do mercado, o ar condicionado Artcool espelhado e o Multi Artcool Gallery. 

A “Casa Conectada LG” ainda conta com demais sofisticados produtos da marca. Confira tudo aqui: lg.com/br/casa-cor

#architecture_hunter 
Tag someone who needs to see this new outstanding project designed by @snohetta 

_project: Reconstruction of harbor bath Knubben 
_architecture: @snohetta 
_visualization: @aesthetica_studio 
_location: Arendal, #Norway 

“Originally designed by architect Ketil Ugland, the facility was used by Arendal Swimming Club for diving competitions, swimming training and other aquatic activities. In 1947, the harbor bath closed its doors before being taken back into use during the 1960s, this time as a jazz club. With its slender and clean lines, Knubben was a small yet elegant example of the modernist spirit. After substantial decay however, the diving platform was demolished by the Norwegian Armed Forces in the 1980s. In 2018, Snøhetta was commissioned to revitalize the facility with a feasibility study. 

The new Knubben is a man-made structure with architecture that draws inspiration from the shapes we find in the islets and skerries along the Norwegian coast. It will resemble a block of stone shaped during the Last Glacial Period, characterized by abraded shapes where soft concave and convex walls form cavities in the landscape. To represent the terrain as accurately as possible, the construction will consist of horizontal layers following the contour lines of a map” say the architects. 

#landscape #landscapedesign #ocean

#architecture_hunter 
Those curvy hanging screens are so interesting! Tag someone who needs to see this project. 

_project: ISSEI Restaurant 
_architecture: @studio.kota 
_photographer: @artipictures 
_location: Jakarta, #Indonesia 

“Located in the heart of Jakarta’s Central Business District Issei is a casual Japanese restaurant by day and sake bar by night. The design is inspired by organic pattern of natural landscape. This idea is translated into free flow curvatures that are applied into the geometry of the seatings and hanging screens. The main dining area is characterized by its double height ceiling space filled with large curvy hanging screens. These semi transparent screens are coordinated with the geometry of the seating layout below to give a consistent visual experience. The dark  dominated color palette combined with warm illumination gives an enigmatic yet warm interior atmosphere. Locally dan naturally sourced materials such as dark stained wood, natural stone and gravel are combined to simulate an experience of being outdoor in the nature”, say the architects. 

#restaurant #restaurantdesign #interiordesign #geometry
